verse.lines:
{lang-eng}The Lord’s my Shepherd, I’ll not want;
He makes me down to lie
In pastures green; He leadeth me
The quiet waters by.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Yea, though I walk in death’s dark vale,
Yet will I fear no ill;
For Thou art with me, and Thy rod
And staff me comfort still.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}My table Thou hast furnished
In presence of my foes;
My head Thou dost with oil anoint,
And my cup overflows.{/lang-eng}
